                "creator": null,
                "video_url": null,
                "description": "Diplomatic Tensions Soar Between India and Canada Over Sikh Separatist Killing The diplomatic row between India and Canada has intensified, with both nations exchanging expulsions of diplomats amid allegations surrounding the killing of Sikh separatist Hardeep Singh Nijjar. Canada's charges against Indian officials have been vehemently denied by New Delhi as politically motivated.Indian envoy to Canada, Sanjay Kumar Verma, has categorically rejected involvement in Nijjar's case, emphasizing the need for legally acceptable evidence, which has yet to be provided by Ottawa, leading to strained bilateral relations.The political drama unfolded further with Canada's accusation of Indian agents in violent activities against pro-Khalistan supporters. Despite failed attempts for evidence-sharing by Canadian officials, India stands firm in demanding substantive proof.",
                "content": "The diplomatic row between India and Canada has intensified, with both nations exchanging expulsions of diplomats amid allegations surrounding the killing of Sikh separatist Hardeep Singh Nijjar. Canada's charges against Indian officials have been vehemently denied by New Delhi as politically motivated. Indian envoy to Canada, Sanjay Kumar Verma, has categorically rejected involvement in Nijjar's case, emphasizing the need for legally acceptable evidence, which has yet to be provided by Ottawa, leading to strained bilateral relations. The political drama unfolded further with Canada's accusation of Indian agents in violent activities against pro-Khalistan supporters. Despite failed attempts for evidence-sharing by Canadian officials, India stands firm in demanding substantive proof. (With inputs from agencies.)",
